#: ../../selection.rst:4
msgid ""
"Selection throughout the Editors of Horizon EDA is very straightforward "
"and there are no surprises here. No matter how basic it seems, the "
"different modes and filters could save you quite some time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:7
msgid "Basics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:11
msgid ""
"Initially, the \"hover select\" mode is active. It simply selects the "
"smallest object under the cursor. Leftclick or drag with the clicked "
"button to select objects permanently. Hit :kbd:`Esc` or click into a "
"blank space for returning to hover select mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:14
msgid ""
"If you want to select multiple things by clicking keep Hit :kbd:`Ctrl` "
"pressed while you click on things â€“ this also works to deselect things "
"you accidentally selected while dragging a selection box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:18
msgid "Selection Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:22
msgid ""
"You can change how dragging the left mouse button behaves in the lower "
"left corner of the editor window. Available are three different modes "
"(Box, Lasso, Paint) with four different selection characteristics (Auto, "
"Include Origin, Touch Box, Include Box)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:26
msgid "Selection Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:30
msgid ""
"If you have to select many things, it can sometimes be handy to only "
"select certain classes of objects. This is what the selection filter is "
"for. You can open it up via the spacebar menu or by pressing :kbd:`Ctrl+i`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../selection.rst:32
msgid ""
"Double click on an item to select only that item. Click on the check mark "
"button on the top left to select all items."
msgstr ""

